  "title": "Tapping to forgive the bad sleep years",
  "subtitle": "A five-minute tapping script for releasing frustration, shame, and body-blame left over from past sleep difficulty.",
  "excerpt": "A five-minute tapping practice from Day 16 of the SLEEP program. The script targets the residue of chronic sleep difficulty: resentment toward the body, shame about the impact, and the accumulated self-criticism of the bad nights.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Adapted from Day 16 of SLEEP: A 30-Day Tapping Program (Rebecca J Page, 2025), \"Forgive the Sleepless Past.\" Tapping framework: Gary Craig's Emotional Freedom Technique (EFT), in use since the mid-1990s, building on Roger Callahan's Thought Field Therapy.",
  "body": {
